The paper deals with object detection using deep neural networks and proposes a novel framework using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate features that provide robustness for object detection on reduced quality images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks and GANs, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed framework on object detection datasets, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
